4:
Lady Orvelle... I wanted to thank you
about that matter we discussed
yesterday. Your contribution to the
orphanage was greatly appreciated!
6:
You needn't thank me. I did little; the
majority of the hard work was put in
by you and your fellows. It is your
accomplishment—be proud of it, my
child.
9:
My lady, you must exercise more
caution when using church funds in
the future... Our coffers are not
endless, after all! What if they were
to run dry?
10:
Whatever am I supposed to report
to the cardinal? I pray that you
continue to remember the
esteemed position you hold and—
15:
I had to listen to him reprimand me
like that for so long... And it was all
because HIS cut of the money was
shrinking!
18:
Agh. As if I don't know all too well
that my position is entirely symbolic.
I have no power to change things!
21:
But if they don't want me to make
decisions, they should really just
stop giving me so much work to do!
Let me REST for once!
30:
Hmm? "That sounds rough"? What a
generic response! You'll have to do
better than that, Master Alk!
35:
Wait a minute. This pillow... It feels
odd to the touch. Firm, but... crunchy?
39:
Whoa! This is quite comfortable!
Master Alk, where did you get this?
42:
Oh, right! That pillow is stuffed with
buckwheat chaff, which is why it's so
crunchy. I got it from a village in
Yamato.
49:
I've made up my mind! I'd like my
own pillow, one of this exact same
type!
54:
Hehe. This must be the way to the
village! Which means I'm one step
closer to my promised pillow!
57:
I get that you're psyched about this,
but don't go running ahead of us, all
right? There are yokai around here.
62: Tsk, what did I tell you?!
72:
Nobody is getting between me and
my pillow! Let's go, everyone!
77:
We're finally at the village, Little Miss
Saint.
92:
I'm... fine... It's just... that path was...
very, very steep... and long! *heave*
97:
It would perhaps be a good idea to
work on your stamina a bit, young
lady!
102:
Hey... It's not my fault! I've spent
most of my waking hours stuck in a
church! It's a wonder my muscles
haven't atrophied!
107:
But I bet you'll be glad you worked
so hard to climb up the mountain.
Take a look!
111:
Today's the day of a special festival.
Our timing was perfect.
116:
Hmm, you know, I've never been to a
festival before... Well, one that I
wasn't forced to attend, at least.
120:
Oh gosh, I might have overdone it... I
think I'm going to vomit...
125:
Huh?! Okay, okay, let's sit you down
somewhere so you can get some
rest!
132:
This festival is wonderful! I managed
to get my hands on some of that
buckwheat chaff, too, so I'm more
than satisfied!
136:
What are those people over there
doing?
139:
That's an ancient Yamato ritual.
They're offering a prayer in thanks
for this year's harvest and wishing
for a bountiful one next year too.
143:
I see. I'm familiar with this sort of
ceremony. I would like to participate
and join them in prayer.
148:
Is that all right? Your faiths are quite
different, would it be okay for
someone of your standing to take
part?
152:
Of course. There's no one from my
church here. And luckily, the Stars
are far more understanding than
most men.
154:
The most important thing is to never
forget to be thankful. We must use
our prayers to convey gratitude.
157:
Faith's ultimate purpose is to share
in happiness and blessings, after all.
164:
Stars, we thank you for leading us,
and for the great blessings you have
provided us.
166:
Continue to guide us Starseekers
down a righteous path.
176:
Oh, don't you mind that! That's just a
side effect of my prayer. It happens
almost every time.
178:
I'm forbidden from selling miracles,
so to speak, so I rarely show off my
abilities. But I felt today was a
special occasion.
181:
How about it? Did this light convince
you I'm actually a saint yet, or what?
184:
It might have... Though I feel like
saints are supposed to be a bit
more humble...
188:
Oh my! Young maiden... Are you a
manifestation of the Kami?!
190:
How fortuitous! We have been
blessed by a maiden from the
heavens!
202:
Oh my gosh! I don't know how to feel
about this! Haha!
209:
Oh... Uh-oh, I think I'm starting to feel
sick again. Oh no, the nausea—
214:
Yikes! Everyone, please put her
down right now!
220: Ahh... This pillow is amazing after all!
223:
Why are you using mine, then? We
went through all that trouble to
make you your own!
227:
I put that one in my bedroom in the
church! I only have one, after all.
That means I'm pillow-less here in
Starview.
230:
Then why not go to the Yamato
village and make another pillow?
233:
No way... Just thinking about
climbing that mountain road again
makes my stomach churn!
237:
Which means, for the foreseeable
future, I'll be loafing around here, in
this room!
241: Make yourself at home, I guess...
